          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Monitor samples were wires of Co/Al alloy (Co:0.46wt%,",
                " 0.381 mm in diameter) and Au/Al alloy (Au: 0.112 wt%,",
                " 0.510 mm in diameter)",
                " Six samples were prepared - three for irradiation",
                " within Cd capsule and other three without Cd.",
                " Standardized solution of 129I including stable",
                " nuclide 127I was used to prepare samples. With Cd",
                " 60 ml of solution was poured into polyethylene",
                " capsule (0.7 mm wall thickness, 1 mm outer diam.,",
                " 40 mm outer length), which in turn was set in cylin-",
                " drical Cd capsule (1 mm wall thickness, 22 mm outer",
                " diam, 63 mm outer length). Without Cd the solution",
                " was diluted 1/10 with distilled water and poured into",
                " another polyethilene capsule.",
                " Two additional potassium-iodine samples were used to",
                " measure the quantity of 127I atoms in 127I-129I",
                " solution."
              ]
            }
          ],
